Your monthly loan repayments take a massive jump. The Reserve Bank has hiked interest rates by a surprising 75 basis points, or three-quarters of a percent. eNCA Business Editor Devan Murugan has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Your monthly loan repayments take a massive jump. The Reserve Bank has hiked interest rates by a surprising 75 basis points, or three-quarters of a percent. Thanks to consecutive interest rate hikes since November last year, much more will come out of your pocket for that home loan too. READ: SARB hikes repo rate to 5.5% Interest rates are still well below what they were before the COVID-19 pandemic. The difference is that many consumers battling other higher costs have much less disposable income than before COVID. There is a silver lining for those with savings though as they will get higher returns on interest. * eNCA Business Editor Devan Murugan reports.